#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&palapeli; is a single-player jigsaw puzzle game. With it you can create and "
"play puzzles ranging from 4 to 10,000 pieces. This version includes "
"facilities to assist in solving large puzzles (300 pieces or more) within "
"the size limits of a computer screen."
msgstr ""
"&palapeli; je izrezljanka za enega igralca. Z njim lahko ustvarjate in "
"igrate izrezljanke, ki obsegajo od 4 do 10.000 kosov. Ta različica vključuje "
"pripomočke za pomoč pri reševanju velikih izrezljank (300 kosov ali več) "
"znotraj omejitev velikosti računalniškega zaslona."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main &palapeli; window is separated into two areas, the puzzle "
"collection and the puzzle table."
msgstr ""
"Glavni okno &palapeli; je razdeljeno na dve področji, zbirko ugank in tabelo "
"uganke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid "This manual continues by describing those two areas."
msgstr "Ta priročnik se nadaljuje z opisom teh dveh področij."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "Browsing the puzzle collection"
msgstr "Brskanje po zbirki ugank"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playing puzzles and updating the collection"
msgstr "Igranje ugank in posodabljanje zbirke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you launch &palapeli; for the first time, your puzzle collection "
"already contains some sample puzzles that come with &palapeli;. Click on one "
"of them to start playing immediately. Later, when you have created some of "
"your own puzzles (see below), you can also click on them to start playing."
msgstr ""
"Ko zaženete &palapeli; prvič, vaša zbirka ugank že vsebuje nekaj vzorčnih "
"ugank, ki so priložene &palapeli;. Kliknite enega od njih, da takoj začnete "
"igrati. Pozneje, ko ustvarite nekaj lastnih ugank (glejte spodaj), jih lahko "
"tudi kliknete, da začnete igrati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Play takes place on the puzzle table; see <link linkend=\"puzzletable\">the "
"section after next</link> for how to use the puzzle table."
msgstr ""
"Igra poteka na izrezljanki; glejte <link linkend=\"puzzletable\">razdelek za "
"naslednjim</link> za uporabo tabele izrezljanke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can select and highlight puzzles in the puzzle list by hold the &Ctrl; "
"key and click with the &LMB;. Pressing the &LMB; or &RMB; without the &Ctrl; "
"key opens that puzzle for playing in the puzzle table."
msgstr ""
"Uganke lahko izberete in označite na seznamu ugank tako, da držite &Ctrl; in "
"kliknite z &LMB;. S pritiskom &LMB; ali &RMB; brez tipke &Ctrl; odpre to "
"uganko za igranje v tabeli uganke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &macOS; you need to double-click with the &LMB; to begin playing. A "
"single click will just select and highlight one entry in the puzzle list."
msgstr ""
"V sistemu &macOS; morate dvoklikniti z &LMB; da začnete igrati. En sam klik "
"bo samo izbral in označil en vnos na seznamu ugank."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As well as playing a puzzle, you can use the puzzle collection for the "
"following actions:"
msgstr ""
"Poleg igranja uganke lahko zbirko ugank uporabite tudi za naslednja dejanja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>create</emphasis> new puzzles from images on your disk"
msgstr "<emphasis>ustvarjanje</emphasis> novih ugank iz slik na vašem disku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>import</emphasis> puzzles made by others"
msgstr "<emphasis>uvozite</emphasis> uganke, ki so jih naredili drugi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>export</emphasis> puzzles to share them with your friends and the "
"world"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Izvozite</emphasis> uganke, da jih delite s prijatelji in svetom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>delete</emphasis> puzzles you do not need any more"
msgstr "<emphasis>izbrišite</emphasis> uganke, ki jih ne potrebujete več"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following section shows how to perform these tasks with the action icons "
"in the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Naslednji razdelek prikazuje, kako izvesti te naloge z ikonami dejanj v "
"orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:80 index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toolbar overview"
msgstr "Pregled orodne vrstice"

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create New Puzzle…"
msgstr "Ustvari novo izrezljanko…"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Opens a dialog which allows you to create a puzzle from an image on "
"your disk.</action> See <link linkend=\"create-puzzles\">the next chapter</"
"link> for details."
msgstr ""
"<action>Odpre pogovorno okno, ki vam omogoča ustvarjanje uganke iz slike na "
"vašem disku.</action> Za podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"create-puzzles"
"\">naslednje poglavje</link>."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete Puzzle"
msgstr "Izbriši izrezljanko"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:90 index.docbook:724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any puzzles that you have selected in the puzzle list, will be permanently "
"deleted from your collection."
msgstr ""
"Vse izrezljanke, ki ste jih izbrali na seznamu izrezljank, bodo trajno "
"izbrisane iz vaše zbirke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:90 index.docbook:724
#, no-c-format
msgid "This action cannot be undone."
msgstr "Tega dejanja ni mogoče razveljaviti."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import from File…"
msgstr "Uvoz iz datoteke…"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:94 index.docbook:716
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>When you have received a &palapeli; puzzle file (which can usually "
"be recognized by the file extension <literal role=\"extension\">.puzzle</"
"literal>), you can use this action to import it into your local collection.</"
"action> Puzzle files can also be played by simply clicking on them in the "
"file manager of your choice, but after the import, the puzzle will appear in "
"your local collection, and you can safely delete the downloaded puzzle file."
msgstr ""
"<action>Ko prejmete &palapeli; datoteko izezljanke (ki jo običajno lahko "
"prepoznate po datotečni priponi <literal role=\"extension\">.puzzle</"
"literal>), lahko uporabite to dejanje, da jo uvozite v svojo lokalno zbirko."
"</action> Datoteke izrezljanke lahko tudi igrate tako, da jih preprosto "
"kliknete v upravitelju datotek po vaši izbiri, vendar se bo po uvozu "
"izrezljanka pojavila v vaši lokalni zbirki in preneseno datoteko izrezljanke "
"lahko varno izbrišete."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export to File…"
msgstr "Izvozi v datoteko…"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:98 index.docbook:720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This will export the currently selected puzzles to files, in order to enable "
"you to give them to your friends, publish them on the web, or make backup "
"copies of your collection."
msgstr ""
"To bo izvozilo trenutno izbrane izrezljanke v datoteke, da jih boste lahko "
"dali prijateljem, objavili na spletu ali naredili varnostne kopije svoje "
"zbirke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating new puzzles"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje novih izrezljank"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "The puzzle creation dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za ustvarjanje izrezljanke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As described in <link linkend=\"toolbar-collection\">the previous section</"
"link>, you can create new puzzles by clicking on the "
"<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"tools-wizard.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject> <guiicon>Create New "
"Puzzle…</guiicon> action icon in the puzzle collection window."
msgstr ""
"Kot je opisano v <link linkend=\"toolbar-collection\">prejšnjem razdelku</"
"link>, lahko ustvarite nove izrezljnke s klikom na "
"<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"tools-wizard.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject> <guiicon>Ustvari novo "
"izrezljanko...</guiicon> ikona dejanja v oknu zbirke izrezljank."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking this action icon opens the puzzle creation dialog, which consists "
"of three pages:"
msgstr ""
"S klikom na to ikono dejanja se odpre pogovorno okno za ustvarjanje "
"izrezljanke, ki je sestavljeno iz treh strani:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the first page, select an image file which will be sliced into pieces. Be "
"sure to enter the correct metadata for the image: You should give "
"attribution to the author of the image (&eg; the photographer or the "
"painter); please respect the copyright of the image author."
msgstr ""
"Na prvi strani izberite slikovno datoteko, ki bo razrezana na dele. "
"Prepričajte se, da ste vnesli pravilne metapodatke za sliko: navesti morate "
"avtorja slike (&eg;. fotografa ali slikarja); spoštujte avtorske pravice "
"avtorja slike."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the second page, you can select the type of pieces into which the image "
"will be sliced. &palapeli; comes with a collection of slicers preinstalled, "
"but third-party slicers may also be available."
msgstr ""
"Na drugi strani lahko izberete vrsto kosov, na katere bo slika razrezana. "
"&palapeli; prihaja z vnaprej nameščeno zbirko rezalnikov, vendar so lahko na "
"voljo tudi rezalniki drugih proizvajalcev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the final page of the dialog, the selected slicer can be customized &eg; "
"by choosing a different piece count or by adjusting parameters of the piece "
"shape. The available set of options depends which slicer has been selected."
msgstr ""
"Na zadnji strani pogovornega okna lahko izbrani rezalnik prilagodite &eg; z "
"izbiro drugega števila kosov ali s prilagoditvijo parametrov oblike kosa. "
"Razpoložljivi nabor možnosti je odvisen od izbranega rezalnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This manual will continue to discuss the slicers which come with &palapeli;. "
"If you have downloaded a third-party slicer plugin for &palapeli;, please "
"refer to the documentation of this plugin if you have trouble installing or "
"using it on your system."
msgstr ""
"Ta priročnik bo še naprej obravnaval rezalnike, ki so priloženi &palapeli;. "
"Če ste prenesli vtičnik rezalnika tretje osebe za &palapeli;, si oglejte "
"dokumentacijo tega vtičnika, če imate težave pri namestitvi ali uporabi v "
"vašem sistemu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simple slicers"
msgstr "Preprosti rezalniki"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&palapeli; has two simple slicers, <guilabel>Classic jigsaw pieces</"
"guilabel> and <guilabel>Rectangular pieces</guilabel>. These slicers create "
"simple rectangular pieces either with or without connecting plugs."
msgstr ""
"&palapeli; ima dva preprosta rezalnika, <guilabel>klasične kose izrezljanke</"
"guilabel> in <guilabel>pravokotne kose</guilabel>. Ti rezalniki ustvarijo "
"preproste pravokotne kose z ali brez priključnih čepov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both slicers allow the piece count and the aspect ratio to be adjusted. "
"Dragging the <guilabel>Piece aspect ratio:</guilabel> slider to the left "
"results in tall pieces, adjusting it to the right produces wide pieces. The "
"default selection produces approximately square pieces."
msgstr ""
"Oba rezalnika omogočata prilagajanje števila kosov in razmerja stranic. Če "
"povlečete drsnik <guilabel>Razmerje stranic:</guilabel> v levo, dobite "
"visoke kose, če ga prilagodite v desno, pa ustvarite široke kose. Privzeti "
"izbor ustvari približno kvadratne kose."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "The advanced &i18n-psc;"
msgstr "Napredni &i18n-psc;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &i18n-psc; produces realistic jigsaw pieces with various basic patterns:"
msgstr ""
"&i18n-psc; izdeluje realistične dele izrezljanke z različnimi osnovnimi "
"vzorci:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rectangular grid"
msgstr "Pravokotna mreža"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Contains the well-known rectangular pieces."
msgstr "Vsebuje dobro znane pravokotne kose."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cairo grid"
msgstr "Kairo mreža"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With its pentagonal pieces and unequal edge angles, it's rather hard to "
"puzzle because the pieces fit together in an unfamiliar manner."
msgstr ""
"S svojimi peterokotnimi kosi in neenakimi robnimi koti je precej težko "
"uganiti, ker se kosi prilegajo skupaj na neznan način."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hexagonal grid"
msgstr "Šesterokotna mreža"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Produces hexagonal pieces, arranged like honeycomb cells."
msgstr "Proizvaja šestkotne koščke, razporejene kot celice satja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rotrex grid"
msgstr "Rotrex mreža"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Through a special composition of triangular, hexagonal and rectangular "
"pieces, the pieces form a pattern resembling to many intersecting circles."
msgstr ""
"S posebno sestavo trikotnih, šesterokotnih in pravokotnih kosov ti tvorijo "
"vzorec, ki spominja na številne sekajoče se kroge."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Irregular grid"
msgstr "Nepravilna mreža"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This grid is available only if you have installed <application>qvoronoi</"
"application> from the <ulink url=\"https://www.qhull.org"
"\"><application>qhull</application> package</ulink>. <application>qvoronoi</"
"application> is used to calculate irregular piece shapes from randomly "
"placed points."
msgstr ""
"Ta mreža je na voljo le, če ste namestili <application>qvoronoi</"
"application> iz paketa <ulink url=\"https://www.qhull.org"
"\"><application>qhull</application></ulink>. <application>qvoronoi</"
"application> se uporablja za izračun nepravilnih oblik kosov iz naključno "
"postavljenih točk."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &i18n-psc; has various parameters which control the appearance of the "
"piece edges, especially the plugs on them. Default settings are provided for "
"all of these parameters. An additional preset mode is available which "
"reduces the amount of parameters to a bare minimum. The following parameters "
"are available usually:"
msgstr ""
"&i18n-psc; ima različne parametre, ki nadzorujejo videz robov kosov, zlasti "
"čepov na njih. Za vse te parametre so na voljo privzete nastavitve. Na voljo "
"je dodatni prednastavljeni način, ki zmanjša število parametrov na najmanjšo "
"možno mero. Običajno so na voljo naslednji parametri:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Piece count:"
msgstr "Število kosov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here set the exact number in which the image will sliced into pieces. This "
"option only appear if the mathematical logic of the slicer selected allows "
"any number."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj nastavite natančno število, v katerem bo slika razrezana na kose. Ta "
"možnost se prikaže le, če matematična logika izbranega rezalnika dovoljuje "
"poljubno število."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Approx. piece count:"
msgstr "Pribl. število kosov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here set the desired number in which the image will sliced into pieces. This "
"option only appears if the mathematical logic of the selected slicer can "
"readjust this number."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj nastavite želeno število, v katerem bo slika razrezana na kose. Ta "
"možnost se prikaže le, če lahko matematična logika izbranega rezalnika "
"ponovno prilagodi to število."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Flipped edge percentage:"
msgstr "Odstotek obrnjenega roba:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The probability for each plug to be flipped. A plug is considered flipped if "
"it points in the opposite direction as it would in a fully regular grid. On "
"the rectangular grid, this results in pieces with 3 or 4 plugs pointing "
"inwards resp. outwards. Position the slider at the very left to obtain the "
"normal fully regular grid. In the middle, plug orientation is random. At the "
"right, the grid is fully regular again, but with an <quote>alternate</quote> "
"rule. This does <emphasis>not</emphasis> mean reversal of all plugs: In the "
"alternate regular grid, for instance, each piece has four inward-pointing or "
"four outward-pointing plugs. This setting has no effect in the irregular "
"grid."
msgstr ""
"Verjetnost, da bo vsak čep obrnjen. Čep se šteje za obrnjenega, če kaže v "
"nasprotni smeri, kot bi bil v povsem pravilni mreži. Na pravokotni mreži to "
"povzroči kose s 3 ali 4 čepki, obrnjenimi navznoter oz. navzven. Postavite "
"drsnik čisto na levo, da dobite običajno popolnoma pravilno mrežo. Na "
"sredini je čep usmerjen naključno. Na desni je mreža spet popolnoma "
"pravilna, vendar z <quote>nadomestnim</quote> pravilom. To <emphasis>ne</"
"emphasis> pomeni obračanje vseh čepkov: v nadomestni pravilni mreži ima na "
"primer vsak kos štiri navznoter obrnjene ali štiri navzven obrnjene čepke. "
"Ta nastavitev nima učinka v nepravilni mreži."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Edge curviness:"
msgstr "Ukrivljenost robov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines how curvy the edges are, &ie; how strongly the borders dent in or "
"bulge out. Move the slider to the very left to obtain straight edge lines "
"(except for the plugs)."
msgstr ""
"Določa, kako ukrivljeni so robovi, &ie; kako močno so robovi vdrti ali "
"izbočeni. Premaknite drsnik čisto v levo, da dobite ravne robne črte (razen "
"za čepke)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Plug size:"
msgstr "Velikost vtiča:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines the size of the plug part of each edge. The default setting "
"(middle position of the slider) is chosen to look like a real puzzle. The "
"slider ranges from 50% to 150% this size, which already looks obscenely "
"large. The program tries very hard to avoid collisions between plugs. "
"Colliding edges are reshaped multiple times and shrinked in small steps. "
"However there still remain cases where no solution can be found, especially "
"for large plug sizes."
msgstr ""
"Določa velikost čepnega dela vsakega roba. Privzeta nastavitev (srednji "
"položaj drsnika) je izbrana tako, da je videti kot prava izrezljanka. Drsnik "
"se giblje od 50 % do 150 % te velikosti, kar je že videti nespodobno veliko. "
"Program se zelo trudi, da bi se izognil kolizijam med čepi. Robovi s trki se "
"večkrat preoblikujejo in krčijo v majhnih korakih. Še vedno pa obstajajo "
"primeri, ko ni mogoče najti rešitve, zlasti za velike velikosti čepov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diversity of curviness:"
msgstr "Raznolikost ukrivljenosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines how much the curviness (see above) varies between edges. Move the "
"slider to the left to make the dents and bulges look all the same. Position "
"the slider at the right, there may occur very curvy and very straight "
"borders."
msgstr ""
"Določa, koliko se ukrivljenost (glejte zgoraj) razlikuje med robovi. "
"Premaknite drsnik v levo, da bodo vdolbine in izbokline videti enake. "
"Postavite drsnik na desno stran, lahko se pojavijo zelo ukrivljene in zelo "
"ravne meje."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diversity of plug position:"
msgstr "Raznolikost položaja čepa:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines how much the position of the plug on the edge varies. Position "
"the slider at the very left, plugs are affixed to the middle of their edge."
msgstr ""
"Določa, koliko se spreminja položaj čepa na robu. Drsnik postavite povsem "
"levo, čepki so pritrjeni na sredino njihovega roba."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diversity of plugs:"
msgstr "Raznolikost vtičnikov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines how individual the plugs look like. Position the slider at the "
"very left, plugs look all the same. At the very right, each plug will be a "
"unique piece of art crafted especially for you."
msgstr ""
"Določa, kako so videti posamezni čepi. Postavite drsnik na čisto levo, čepi "
"so videti enaki. Čisto desno bo vsak čep edinstvena umetnina, izdelana "
"posebej za vas."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diversity of piece size:"
msgstr "Raznolikost velikosti kosov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only for irregular grid: Determines how the piece size varies. A very small "
"setting means nearly no variation; crystallite-like structure arise. Higher "
"settings produce very small and very large pieces."
msgstr ""
"Samo za nepravilno mrežo: Določa, kako se spreminja velikost kosa. Zelo "
"majhna nastavitev pomeni skoraj nobeno spremembo; nastane kristalitom "
"podobna struktura. Višje nastavitve proizvajajo zelo majhne in zelo velike "
"kose."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dump grid image:"
msgstr "Slika mreže izpisa:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save an image of the grid (black edges on white background) at <filename>~/"
"goldberg-slicer-dump.png</filename>. If a previous dump exists, it is "
"overwritten."
msgstr ""
"Shranite sliko mreže (črni robovi na belem ozadju) na <filename>~/goldberg-"
"slicer-dump.png</filename>. Če prejšnji izpis obstaja, je prepisan."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:194
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playing on the puzzle table"
msgstr "Igranje na mizi z izrezljankami"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic moves"
msgstr "Osnovne poteze"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:200
#, no-c-format
msgid "The puzzle table (detail)"
msgstr "Miza z izrezljankami (podrobnost)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "The goal of the game is to assemble the given pieces into an image."
msgstr "Cilj igre je sestaviti dane dele v sliko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The floating Preview window shows you what that image should be. Use a "
"toolbar or menu item to show or hide the window. For a detailed description, "
"see <link linkend=\"puzzletable-preview\">The Preview window</link>."
msgstr ""
"Lebdeče okno za predogled vam pokaže, kakšna naj bo ta slika. Za prikaz ali "
"skrivanje okna uporabite orodno vrstico ali menijski element. Za podroben "
"opis glejte <link linkend=\"puzzletable-preview\">Okno za predogled</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you wish to attempt a puzzle that has 300 or more pieces, please read the "
"chapter on <link linkend=\"large-puzzles\">Facilities for solving large "
"puzzles</link>, after you have read this chapter."
msgstr ""
"Če želite poskusiti sestaviti izrezljanko, ki ima 300 ali več kosov, "
"preberite poglavje o <link linkend=\"large-puzzles\">Možnosti za reševanje "
"velikih izrezljank</link>, potem ko ste prebrali to poglavje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can move a single piece by clicking and dragging it with the &LMB;. That "
"will leave the piece selected and highlighted. To move several pieces at "
"once, first select and highlight them, then click and drag just one of the "
"pieces. The rest will follow."
msgstr ""
"Posamezen kos lahko premaknete tako, da ga kliknete in povlečete z &LMB;. "
"Tako bo del izbran in poudarjen. Če želite premakniti več kosov hkrati, jih "
"najprej izberite in označite, nato kliknite in povlecite samo enega od "
"kosov. Ostalo bo sledilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can select and highlight multiple pieces by holding &Ctrl; and clicking "
"on them, or by dragging a rubberband around them with the &LMB;. You can "
"also hold the &Ctrl; key and click with the &LMB; to increase or decrease "
"the current selection one piece at a time."
msgstr ""
"Več kosov lahko izberete in označite tako, da držite &Ctrl; in jih kliknete "
"ali pa z &LMB; povlečete gumijasti trak okoli njih. Lahko tudi držite &Ctrl; "
"in kliknite z &LMB; za povečanje ali zmanjšanje trenutne izbire en del "
"naenkrat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove selection and highlighting, just click on an empty spot on the "
"puzzle table or on a piece that is not already selected."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odstraniti izbor in označevanje, samo kliknite na prazno mesto na "
"mizi izrezljanke ali na kosu, ki še ni izbran."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you put one piece near a neighboring piece, both pieces will "
"automatically snap together and become joined (1). After pieces have been "
"snapped together, they cannot be torn apart. Another difference between "
"&palapeli; and a real-world jigsaw puzzle is that you cannot combine two "
"pieces that are not true neighbors."
msgstr ""
"Ko postavite en kos blizu sosednjega kosa, se bosta oba kosa samodejno "
"zaskočila skupaj in postala združena (1). Ko so deli sestavljeni skupaj, jih "
"ni več mogoče raztrgati. Druga razlika med &palapeli; in resnična "
"izrezljanka je, da ne morete združiti dveh kosov, ki nista prava soseda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The progress bar below the puzzle table indicates your progress by counting "
"joined pieces (2). &palapeli; will automatically save your progress after "
"every move, so you do not have to worry about saving."
msgstr ""
"Vrstica napredka pod tabelo uganke prikazuje vaš napredek s štetjem "
"združenih kosov (2). &palapeli; samodejno shrani vaš napredek po vsaki "
"potezi, tako da vam ni treba skrbeti za shranjevanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can zoom the puzzle table view in or out with the mouse "
"<mousebutton>wheel</mousebutton>, and at the bottom right (3) with the "
"buttons and the slider."
msgstr ""
"Pogled tabele izrezljanke lahko povečate ali pomanjšate z miškinim "
"<mousebutton>koleščkom</mousebutton>, desno spodaj (3) pa z gumbi in "
"drsnikom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can move the puzzle table view in any direction by clicking and dragging "
"with the &RMB;."
msgstr ""
"Pogled tabele izrezljank lahko premaknete v katero koli smer s klikom in "
"vlečenjem z &RMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The movement of the pieces is limited by the <emphasis>puzzle table area</"
"emphasis>. This area is represented on the puzzle table's background by a "
"light rectangular shade. When you move pieces to the border (4) of the "
"puzzle table area, the area will automatically expand to give you more space "
"for moving your puzzle pieces. Near the shaded borders, the mouse cursor "
"changes into a double-headed arrow, indicating that you can adjust the "
"puzzle table area by clicking there and dragging with the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Gibanje kosov je omejeno z <emphasis>območjem mize izrezljank</emphasis>. To "
"območje je na ozadju mize izrezljanke predstavljeno s svetlim pravokotnim "
"odtenkom. Ko premaknete kose na rob (4) območja mize izrezljank, se bo "
"območje samodejno razširilo, da boste imeli več prostora za premikanje kosov "
"izrezljanke. Blizu zasenčenih robov se kazalec miške spremeni v dvosmerno "
"puščico, kar pomeni, da lahko prilagodite območje mize izrezljank, tako da "
"tam kliknete in povlečete z &LMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can lock the puzzle table area with the small button (5) to the right of "
"the progress bar. The shade (4) around the puzzle table will darken, and "
"pieces will now stop moving at the edges of the puzzle table area. It is "
"still possible to adjust the size of the puzzle table area manually."
msgstr ""
"Območje mize izrezljanke lahko zaklenete z majhnim gumbom (5) desno od "
"vrstice napredka. Senca (4) okoli mize izrezljank bo potemnela in kosi se "
"bodo prenehali premikati na robovih mize izrezljank. Še vedno je mogoče "
"ročno prilagoditi velikost območja mize izrezljanke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Preview window"
msgstr "Okno predogleda"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Preview is a small window that floats above or to one side of the puzzle "
"table window. It contains an image of the completed puzzle: the picture that "
"would appear on top of the box if this was a real-world jigsaw puzzle."
msgstr ""
"Predogled je majhno okno, ki lebdi nad ali ob eni strani okna mize "
"izrezljanke. Vsebuje sliko dokončane izrezljanke: sliko, ki bi se pojavila "
"na vrhu škatle, če bi bila to izrezljanka iz resničnega sveta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The window can be shown or hidden by using the "
"<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"view-preview.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject> <guiicon>Preview</"
"guiicon> action icon in the toolbar or the <menuchoice><guimenu>View</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Preview</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. Its "
"size, position and visible or not visible setting are saved and restored "
"between runs of &palapeli;."
msgstr ""
"Okno lahko prikažete ali skrijete z "
"<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"view-preview.png\" "
"format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject></inlinemediaobject> <guiicon>Predogled</"
"guiicon> ikone dejanja v orodni vrstici ali menijski element "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Pogled</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Predogled</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>. Njegova velikost, položaj in vidna ali nevidna nastavitev se "
"shranijo in obnovijo med zagoni &palapeli;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Being a window, it can be freely moved around the desktop and resized. Its "
"<guibutton>Close</guibutton> button will hide it and its "
"<guibutton>Maximize</guibutton> button will expand or contract the picture "
"rapidly."
msgstr ""
"Ker je okno, ga je mogoče prosto premikati po namizju in spreminjati njegovo "
"velikost. Njegov gumb <guibutton>Zapri</guibutton> ga bo skril, gumb "
"<guibutton>Razpni</guibutton> pa bo sliko hitro razširil ali skrčil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Preview window has a magnification feature, so it need not take up much "
"space. If you move the mouse over the window, it zooms in quickly to reveal "
"a magnified view of the area under the mouse and the equivalent of a few "
"pieces around it. This is very useful for viewing details of the puzzle and "
"identifying pieces you have found, but it can be tricky to control, "
"especially near the edges of the picture."
msgstr ""
"Okno za predogled ima funkcijo povečave, zato vam ni treba zavzeti veliko "
"prostora. Če premaknete miško čez okno, se hitro poveča in razkrije povečan "
"pogled na območje pod miško in enakovredno nekaj kosov okoli njega. To je "
"zelo uporabno za ogled podrobnosti izrezljanke in prepoznavanje kosov, ki "
"ste jih našli, vendar ga je lahko težko nadzorovati, zlasti ob robovih slike."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mouse interactions"
msgstr "Interakcije z miško"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As described in the previous section, there are plenty of ways to interact "
"with &palapeli;'s puzzle table using the mouse. You can configure freely "
"which actions are triggered by which mouse buttons. (See <link linkend="
"\"configuration-mouseactions\">Game Configuration</link> section for more "
"information on how to configure this.) The following list summarizes all "
"possible mouse actions:"
msgstr ""
"Kot je opisano v prejšnjem razdelku, obstaja veliko načinov za interakcijo z "
"mizo izrezljanke &palapeli; z uporabo miške. Poljubno lahko konfigurirate, "
"katera dejanja sprožijo kateri gumbi miške. (Glejte razdelek <link linkend="
"\"configuration-mouseactions\">Konfiguracija igre</link> za več informacij o "
"tem, kako to konfigurirati.) Naslednji seznam povzema vsa možna dejanja "
"miške:"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change size of puzzle table area by dragging its edges"
msgstr ""
"Spremenite velikost območja mize izrezljanke tako, da povlečete njene robove"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, this action is assigned to the &LMB;."
msgstr "Privzeto je to dejanje dodeljeno &LMB;."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "Move pieces by dragging"
msgstr "Premikaj kose z vlečenjem"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click and drag a puzzle piece, this piece will be moved. If "
"multiple pieces have been selected and you click and drag one of these "
"pieces, then all pieces are moved. By default, this action is assigned to "
"the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Ko kliknete in povlečete kos izrezljanke, se ta premakne. Če je bilo "
"izbranih več kosov in kliknete in povlečete enega od teh kosov, se vsi deli "
"premaknejo. Privzeto je to dejanje dodeljeno &LMB;."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "Move viewport by dragging"
msgstr "Premaknite vidno polje z vlečenjem"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This action moves the view of the entire puzzle table in any direction. By "
"default, it is assigned to the &RMB;."
msgstr ""
"To dejanje premakne pogled celotne mize izrezljanke v katero koli smer. "
"Privzeto je dodeljen &RMB;."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select several pieces by rubber banding"
msgstr "Izberite več kosov z gumijastim trakom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click on a free area of the puzzle table instead of a puzzle piece, "
"you can drag a rubberband. When you let the mouse button go, all pieces "
"inside the rubberband are selected. All other pieces are deselected. By "
"default, this action is assigned to the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Ko namesto kosa izrezljanke kliknete na prosto območje mize izrezljanke, "
"lahko povlečete gumijasti trak. Ko spustite gumb miške, so izbrani vsi kosi "
"znotraj gumijastega traku. Vsi drugi deli so preklicani. Privzeto je to "
"dejanje dodeljeno &LMB;."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select multiple pieces at once"
msgstr "Izberite več kosov hkrati"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:271
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click on a puzzle piece, it will be selected or, if it was already "
"selected, it will be deselected. It can also be used to adjust a rubberband "
"selection. By default, this action is assigned to the &LMB; and only "
"available when &Ctrl; is pressed."
msgstr ""
"Ko kliknete del izrezljanke, bo izbran ali, če je bil že izbran, bo "
"preklican. Uporablja se lahko tudi za prilagajanje izbire gumijastega traku. "
"Privzeto je to dejanje dodeljeno &LMB; in na voljo samo, ko je tipka &Ctrl; "
"pritisnjena."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clear selections and highlighting"
msgstr "Počisti izbire in označevanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click on an empty spot in the puzzle table or on a piece that is not already "
"selected."
msgstr ""
"Kliknite na prazno mesto na mizi izrezljanke ali na kos, ki še ni izbran."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:278
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zoom the puzzle table view in or out"
msgstr "Povečajte ali pomanjšajte pogled mize izrezljanke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This action is identical to clicking the buttons either side of the slider "
"(3) on the status bar. It is assigned to the mouse <mousebutton>wheel</"
"mousebutton> by default."
msgstr ""
"To dejanje je enako klikanju gumbov na obeh straneh drsnika (3) v vrstici "
"stanja. Privzeto je dodeljen <mousebutton>kolescu</mousebutton> miške."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switch to close-up or distant view"
msgstr "Preklopite na pogled od blizu ali na daljavo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This action alternates (toggles) between a close-up and distant view, at the "
"position of the mouse pointer. It is intended mainly to provide fast zooming "
"in large puzzles (300 pieces or more). For more detail, see <link linkend="
"\"large-puzzle-fast-zooming\">Fast zooming between close-up and distant "
"view</link>. By default, the action is assigned to the &MMB;."
msgstr ""
"To dejanje preklaplja (preklaplja) med pogledom od blizu in oddaljenim "
"pogledom na položaju kazalca miške. Namenjen je predvsem zagotavljanju "
"hitrega približevanja velikih izrezljank (300 kosov ali več). Za več "
"podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"large-puzzle-fast-zooming\">Hitro "
"povečevanje med pogledom od blizu in oddaljenim pogledom</link>. Privzeto je "
"dejanje dodeljeno &MMB;."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Teleport pieces to or from a holder"
msgstr "Teleportirajte kose na držalo ali iz njega"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This action helps you collect, sort and move pieces rapidly in large puzzles "
"(300 pieces or more) without dragging and dropping. You can use it in "
"smaller puzzles if you wish. For more detail, see <link linkend=\"large-"
"puzzle-holders\">Using piece-holders</link>. By default, the action is "
"assigned to the &LMB; and only available when &Shift; key is pressed."
msgstr ""
"To dejanje vam pomaga hitro zbirati, razvrščati in premikati koščke v "
"velikih izrezljankah (300 kosov ali več) brez vlečenja in spuščanja. Če "
"želite, ga lahko uporabite v manjših izrezljankah. Za več podrobnosti glejte "
"<link linkend=\"large-puzzle-holders\">Uporaba držal za kose</link>. "
"Privzeto je dejanje dodeljeno &LMB; in na voljo le, ko je tipka &Shift; "
"pritisnjena."

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle lock state of the puzzle table area"
msgstr "Preklopi zaklenjeno stanje območja mize izrezljanke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This action is identical to pressing the button (5) on the status bar. By "
"default, this action is not assigned to any mouse button, but you can enable "
"it from <link linkend=\"configuration-mouseactions\">the configuration "
"dialog</link>."
msgstr ""
"To dejanje je enako pritisku gumba (5) v statusni vrstici. To dejanje "
"privzeto ni dodeljeno nobenemu gumbu miške, vendar ga lahko omogočite v "
"<link linkend=\"configuration-mouseactions\">konfiguracijskem pogovornem "
"oknu</link>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Scroll viewport horizontally</action> and <action>Scroll viewport "
"vertically</action>"
msgstr ""
"<action>Pomikaj se po oknu vodoravno</action> in <action>Pomikaj se po oknu "
"navpično</action>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, this action is not assigned to the mouse <mousebutton>wheel</"
"mousebutton>, but you can enable it from <link linkend=\"configuration-"
"mouseactions\">the configuration dialog</link>."
msgstr ""
"To dejanje privzeto ni dodeljeno <mousebutton>kolescu</mousebutton> miške, "
"vendar ga lahko omogočite v <link linkend=\"configuration-mouseactions"
"\">konfiguracijskem pogovornem oknu</link>."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid "Back to Collection"
msgstr "Nazaj v zbirko"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305 index.docbook:752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Go back to the collection to choose another puzzle.</action> Can be "
"used only when you are solving a puzzle."
msgstr ""
"<action>Pojdite nazaj v zbirko, da izberete drugo izrezljanko.</action> "
"Uporabite ga lahko samo, ko rešujete izrezljanko."

#. Tag: guiicon
#: index.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preview"
msgstr "Predogled"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle the display of the preview window with the completed puzzle."
msgstr "Preklopi prikaz predoglednega okna z dokončano izrezljanko."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid "Facilities for solving large puzzles"
msgstr "Pripomočki za reševanje velikih izrezljank"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "General principles"
msgstr "Splošna načela"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&palapeli; can handle large puzzles from 300 to 10,000 pieces, but you need "
"some special facilities to help you work with them on a small screen."
msgstr ""
"&palapeli; lahko obravnava velike izrezljanke od 300 do 10.000 kosov, vendar "
"potrebujete nekaj posebnih pripomočkov za pomoč pri delu z njimi na majhnem "
"zaslonu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can create a large puzzle in exactly the same way as a smaller puzzle. "
"See the chapter on <link linkend=\"create-puzzles\">Creating new puzzles</"
"link>, but there are some things you need to think about before you begin. "
"For details see <link linkend=\"large-puzzle-creation\">Creating large "
"puzzles - special concerns</link>."
msgstr ""
"Veliko izrezljanko lahko sestavite na povsem enak način kot manjšo "
"izrezljanko. Oglejte si poglavje o <link linkend=\"create-puzzles"
"\">Ustvarjanju novih izrezljank</link>, vendar je nekaj stvari, o katerih "
"morate razmisliti, preden začnete. Za podrobnosti glejte <link linkend="
"\"large-puzzle-creation\">Ustvarjanje velikih izrezljank – posebne skrbi</"
"link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Preview window is very useful in large puzzles: see the section about it "
"for a <link linkend=\"puzzletable-preview\">detailed description</link>."
msgstr ""
"Okno za predogled je zelo uporabno pri velikih izrezljankah; glejte razdelek "
"o njem za <link linkend=\"puzzletable-preview\">podroben opis</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Managing space and moving around are your next concerns. When you zoom out "
"to view the whole puzzle table, it becomes hard to see individual pieces. If "
"you zoom in and find a piece you are looking for, it is unlikely that the "
"place where it goes will be visible in the view. See the <link linkend="
"\"large-puzzle-space\">Managing space and moving around</link> section for "
"some solutions to these problems and others."
msgstr ""
"Upravljanje prostora in premikanje sta vaši naslednji skrbi. Ko pomanjšate, "
"da si ogledate celotno mizo izrezljanke, postane težko videti posamezne "
"dele. Če povečate in najdete kos, ki ga iščete, je malo verjetno, da bo "
"mesto, kamor gre, vidno v pogledu. Oglejte si razdelek <link linkend=\"large-"
"puzzle-space\">Upravljanje prostora in premikanje</link> za nekatere rešitve "
"teh in drugih težav."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, you need to collect pieces and convey them to your solution area in "
"some more efficient way than repetitive dragging and dropping over large "
"distances. This is where piece-holders come in."
msgstr ""
"Končno morate zbrati koščke in jih prenesti na območje rešitve na "
"učinkovitejši način kot ponavljajoče se vlečenje in spuščanje na velike "
"razdalje. Tu pridejo na vrsto držala kosov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you start a large puzzle, you are given a holder (a small floating "
"window) called <quote>Hand</quote> into which you can put pieces when and "
"wherever you see them. Then you can drop them near your solution and work "
"out where each piece has to go. This is like collecting pieces in one hand "
"as you scan a large real-world jigsaw puzzle."
msgstr ""
"Ko začnete sestavljati veliko izrezljanko, dobite držalo (majhno lebdeče "
"okno), imenovano <quote>Roka</quote>, v katerega lahko vstavite koščke, "
"kadar koli in kjer koli jih vidite. Nato jih lahko odložite blizu svoje "
"rešitve in ugotovite, kam mora posamezen kos iti. To je kot zbiranje kosov v "
"eni roki, ko prečesavate veliko izrezljanke iz resničnega sveta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may need some systematic way to collect and sort pieces by common "
"attributes (&eg; edges, sky, skyline, &etc;) and so you can use as many "
"holders as you like and give them names. Holders are saved continually, "
"along with the puzzle table, which means you can use them to build up parts "
"of the solution and store them or even to store pieces that you wish to put "
"into a <quote>too hard basket</quote> until later. For details on how to use "
"holders see the <link linkend=\"large-puzzle-holders\">Using piece-holders</"
"link> section."
msgstr ""
"Morda boste potrebovali nekaj sistematičnega načina za zbiranje in "
"razvrščanje kosov po skupnih atributih (&eg; robovi, nebo, obzorje &etc;), "
"tako da lahko uporabite poljubno število držal in jim daste imena. Držala se "
"nenehno shranjujejo skupaj z mizo izrezljanke, kar pomeni, da jih lahko "
"uporabite za sestavljanje delov rešitve in njihovo shranjevanje ali celo za "
"shranjevanje kosov, ki jih želite dati v <quote>pretrdo košaro</quote> za "
"pozneje. Za podrobnosti o uporabi držal glejte razdelek <link linkend="
"\"large-puzzle-holders\">Uporaba držal kosov</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, the <link linkend=\"puzzletable-mouseactions\">Mouse interactions</"
"link> section lists the two special mouse actions that make working with "
"large puzzles quicker and easier: teleporting pieces and zooming to close-up "
"or distant view."
msgstr ""
"Nazadnje, razdelek <link linkend=\"puzzletable-mouseactions\">Interakcije z "
"miško</link> navaja dve posebni dejanji miške, ki omogočata hitrejše in "
"lažje delo z velikimi izrezljankami: teleportiranje kosov in povečavo na "
"pogled od blizu ali na daljavo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating large puzzles - special concerns"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje velikih izrezljank - posebne skrbi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you create a large puzzle, you should make sure that the image in "
"your source contains enough detail (&ie; enough megapixels). You can use a "
"file utility or photo viewer/editor to find out how many pixels wide and "
"high your picture is when not compressed by JPEG or other image format. As a "
"rough rule of thumb, allow one megapixel per 1,000 pieces. That will give "
"each piece about 1,000 pixels or more than 30 by 30 pixels, making the "
"pieces reasonably sharp at the edges and clear to see when you zoom in. You "
"can work with fewer megapixels, but it may be hard to distinguish and "
"recognize pieces during play."
msgstr ""
"Preden ustvarite veliko izrezljanko, se morate prepričati, da slika v vašem "
"viru vsebuje dovolj podrobnosti (tj. dovolj megapikslov). Uporabite lahko "
"pripomoček za datoteke ali pregledovalnik/urejevalnik fotografij, da "
"ugotovite, koliko slikovnih pik je široka in visoka vaša slika, ko ni "
"stisnjena z JPEG ali drugim formatom slike. Kot grobo pravilo dovolite en "
"megapiksel na 1000 kosov. Tako bo vsak kos imel približno 1000 slikovnih pik "
"ali več kot 30 krat 30 slikovnih pik, zaradi česar bodo kosi razmeroma ostri "
"na robovih in jasno vidni, ko jih povečate. Delate lahko z manj megapiksli, "
"vendar bo morda težko razlikovati in prepoznati dele med igro."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you create or restart a large puzzle, it may be best to avoid using the "
"bevel and shadowing features of &palapeli; (see the <link linkend="
"\"configuration-general\">General settings</link> section), because they "
"make loading slower and highlighting harder to see when the pieces in the "
"view are very small. More prominent highlighting appears when shadowing is "
"not used."
msgstr ""
"Ko ustvarite ali znova zaženete veliko izrezljanko, je morda najbolje, da se "
"izognete uporabi funkcij za poševni položaj in senčenje &palapeli; (glejte "
"razdelek <link linkend=\"configuration-general\">Splošne nastavitve</link>), "
"ker je zaradi njih nalaganje počasnejše in je označevanje težje videti, ko "
"so deli v pogledu zelo majhni. Ko senčenje ni uporabljeno, se pojavi "
"izrazitejši poudarek."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing space and moving around"
msgstr "Urejanje prostora in gibanje"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allocating space on the puzzle table"
msgstr "Dodeljevanje prostora na mizi z izrezljankami"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you create or restart a puzzle, the pieces are shuffled and placed "
"randomly into grid locations on the puzzle table. Two settings affect the "
"space required, see <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game Configuration</"
"link> for a list of settings provided via <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Configure &palapeli;…</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> or, "
"on &macOS;, <menuchoice><guimenu>&palapeli;</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Preferences…</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Ko ustvarite ali znova zaženete izrezljanko, se deli premešajo in naključno "
"postavijo na mrežna mesta na mizi izrezljanke. Dve nastavitvi vplivata na "
"potreben prostor, glejte <link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija igre</"
"link> za seznam nastavitev, ki so na voljo prek "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj "
"&palapeli;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> ali v &macOS;, "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>&palapeli;</guimenu> element menija "
"<guimenuitem>Preference...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The spacing of pieces in puzzle grids can be set from 1.0 to 1.5 times the "
"height and width of the highest and widest pieces. Smaller settings pack the "
"pieces into the view better, but larger ones allow more space for dragging, "
"dropping and rubber banding. The default is 1.3, but 1.1 is very workable in "
"large puzzles. The setting applies to puzzles of all sizes, and also affects "
"grids used with piece-holders (see <link linkend=\"large-puzzle-holders"
"\">Using piece-holders</link>) or when re-arranging pieces automatically on "
"the puzzle table, using the <menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>R</keycap></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem>Rearrange Pieces</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Razmik kosov v mrežah izrezljank je mogoče nastaviti od 1,0 do 1,5-kratne "
"višine in širine najvišjih in najširših kosov. Manjše nastavitve bolje "
"zapakirajo dele v pogled, večje pa omogočajo več prostora za vlečenje, "
"spuščanje in gumijaste trakove. Privzeta vrednost je 1.3, vendar je 1.1 zelo "
"uporaben pri velikih izrezljankah. Nastavitev velja za izrezljanke vseh "
"velikosti in vpliva tudi na mreže, ki se uporabljajo z držali kosov (glejte "
"<link linkend=\"large-puzzle-holders\">Uporaba držal kosov</link>) ali pri "
"samodejnem prerazporejanju kosov na mizo izrezljanke z uporabo menijske "
"postavke <menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>R</keycap></shortcut> "
"<guimenu>Premakni</guimenu><guimenuitem>Prerazporedi koščke</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The other setting provides space on the puzzle table of exactly the right "
"size for building your solution. The default is for it to appear in the "
"center, with the pieces distributed evenly around the outside. On average, "
"this should put the pieces closest to where they have to go eventually. You "
"can also choose to use any of the four corners or have no space (option "
"<guilabel>None</guilabel>), in which case you have to clear space manually, "
"perhaps by expanding the puzzle table area (see <link linkend=\"puzzletable-"
"moves\">Basic moves</link>). The solution space setting affects puzzles down "
"to 20 pieces, but with fewer than 20 pieces solution spaces are pointless."
msgstr ""
"Druga nastavitev zagotavlja prostor na mizi izrezljanke točno prave "
"velikosti za izdelavo vaše rešitve. Privzeto je, da se prikaže v sredini, "
"kosi pa so enakomerno razporejeni po zunanji strani. V povprečju bi to "
"moralo postaviti kose najbližje mestu, kamor morajo sčasoma priti. Lahko se "
"tudi odločite za uporabo katerega koli od štirih vogalov ali pa nimate "
"prostora (možnost <guilabel>Brez</guilabel>), v tem primeru morate prostor "
"počistiti ročno, morda tako, da razširite območje mize izrezljanke (glejte "
"<link linkend= \"puzzletable-moves\">Osnovne poteze</link>). Nastavitev "
"prostora za rešitve vpliva na izrezljanke do 20 kosov, vendar z manj kot 20 "
"kosi so prostori za rešitve nesmiselni."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:454
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As the puzzle solution progresses, pieces move into the solution area and "
"leave spaces elsewhere. It may be helpful to pack the remaining pieces "
"closer together. If so, select some pieces using rubber banding or hold the "
"&Ctrl; key and click with the &LMB;, then use the "
"<menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>R</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Rearrange Pieces</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item or simply "
"the shortcut (default is the <keycap>R</keycap> key). The pieces are packed "
"into a grid and remain selected, so that they can be easily moved to a "
"better position, if required. This is also a way to gather together pieces "
"with some common attribute, but using piece-holders is more powerful."
msgstr ""
"Ko reševanje izrezljanke napreduje, se deli premaknejo v območje rešitve in "
"pustijo prostore drugje. Morda bi bilo koristno, če preostale dele "
"zapakirate bližje skupaj. Če je tako, izberite nekaj kosov z uporabo "
"gumijastih trakov ali držite tipko &Ctrl; in kliknite z &LMB;, nato "
"uporabite <menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>R</keycap></shortcut> "
"<guimenu>Premakni</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Prerazporedi kose</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> element menija ali preprosto bližnjico (privzeto je tipka "
"<keycap>R</keycap>). Kosi so zapakirani v mrežo in ostanejo izbrani, tako da "
"jih je mogoče enostavno premakniti na boljši položaj, če je potrebno. To je "
"tudi način za zbiranje kosov z nekaterimi skupnimi lastnostmi, vendar je "
"uporaba držal za kose močnejša."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fast zooming between close-up and distant view"
msgstr "Hitro povečevanje med pogledom od blizu in oddaljenim pogledom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a puzzle is loaded, &palapeli; calculates distant and close-up views "
"and displays the distant view, which shows the entire puzzle table area. The "
"close-up view shows pieces at a convenient viewing size for your eyes and "
"your screen and desktop. Use the &MMB; to switch quickly between the two "
"views, at a location where the mouse is pointing. Then you can home in "
"quickly on any piece in the puzzle table and see what shape it is and what "
"part of the picture it contains."
msgstr ""
"Ko je izrezljanka naložena, &palapeli; izračuna oddaljene in bližnje poglede "
"ter prikaže oddaljeni pogled, ki prikazuje celotno območje mize izrezljanke. "
"Pogled od blizu prikazuje dele v primerni velikosti za vaše oči ter zaslon "
"in namizje. Uporabite &MMB; za hitro preklapljanje med obema pogledoma na "
"mestu, kamor kaže miška. Nato se lahko hitro obrnete na kateri koli kos v "
"mizi izrezljanke in vidite, kakšne oblike je in kateri del slike vsebuje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:486
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can adjust the scale of either view by zooming manually and your setting "
"will be remembered next time you switch the view by using the &MMB;. Puzzles "
"of all sizes have the fast zooming feature, but in puzzles with less than "
"100 pieces the two views are almost the same as each other. In other words, "
"the pieces are easy to see when you view the whole puzzle table."
msgstr ""
"Merilo enega ali drugega pogleda lahko prilagodite z ročnim zoomiranjem in "
"vaša nastavitev se bo spomnila, ko naslednjič preklopite pogled z &MMB;. "
"Izrezljanke vseh velikosti imajo funkcijo hitrega povečave, vendar sta pri "
"izrezljankah z manj kot 100 kosi pogleda skoraj enaka. Z drugimi besedami, "
"koščke je enostavno videti, ko si ogledate celotno mizo izrezljanke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving around in a large puzzle"
msgstr "Premikanje v veliki izrezljanki"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The hard way to move pieces in a large puzzle is to select them and then "
"alternately drag the pieces and the puzzle table (&LMB; and &RMB;) until you "
"get to your destination. A much easier way to do the same thing is to select "
"the pieces, zoom to distant view (&MMB;, see above), drag the pieces to the "
"destination in one move (&LMB;) and then zoom to close-up view (&MMB;). This "
"is also a good way to retrieve a single stray piece, but dragging that tiny "
"piece across the puzzle table, without losing the selection, can be tricky "
"if there are thousands of pieces."
msgstr ""
"Težji način za premikanje kosov v veliki izrezljanki je, da jih izberete in "
"nato izmenično povlečete koščke in mizo izrezljanke (&LMB; in &RMB;), dokler "
"ne pridete do cilja. Veliko lažji način za isto stvar je, da izberete dele, "
"povečate na oddaljeni pogled (&MMB;, glejte zgoraj), povlečete dele na cilj "
"z eno potezo (&LMB;) in nato povečate na pogled od blizu (&MMB;). To je tudi "
"dober način za pridobivanje enega samega potepuškega koščka, vendar je lahko "
"vlečenje tega majhnega koščka po mizi izrezljanke, ne da bi izgubili izbor, "
"težavno, če je kosov na tisoče."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another way to navigate and search the puzzle table systematically is to "
"zoom in on the top left corner (&MMB;), then use the empty spaces in the "
"scroll bars to step through the table horizontally or vertically, one fixed-"
"size <quote>page</quote> at a time. This technique is very effective when "
"you are using piece-holders to collect pieces you are looking for. If you "
"keep the close-up scale fixed and always start at the same place, you will "
"always get <quote>pages</quote> of fixed size and contents."
msgstr ""
"Drug način sistematičnega krmarjenja in iskanja po mizi izrezljanke je "
"povečava zgornjega levega kota (&MMB;), nato pa uporabite prazne prostore v "
"drsnih trakovih za vodoravno ali navpično premikanje po mizi, po ena "
"<quote>stran fiksne velikosti </quote> naenkrat. Ta tehnika je zelo "
"učinkovita, ko za zbiranje kosov, ki jih iščete, uporabljate držala za kose. "
"Če ohranite merilo od blizu in vedno začnete na istem mestu, boste vedno "
"dobili <quote>strani</quote> fiksne velikosti in vsebine."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:525
#, no-c-format
msgid "Visibility of pieces in large puzzles"
msgstr "Vidnost kosov v velikih izrezljankah"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In large jigsaw puzzles on a small screen it can be hard to see what you are "
"doing. For example, with a 10,000 piece puzzle on a 1440 by 900 screen, the "
"pieces in the distant view of the puzzle table are about 7 pixels across. At "
"this scale, it is hard to see picture, color, piece-shape or even "
"highlighting."
msgstr ""
"Pri velikih izrezljankah na majhnem zaslonu je težko videti, kaj počnete. Na "
"primer, pri izrezljanki z 10.000 kosi na zaslonu velikosti 1440 x 900 so "
"kosi v oddaljenem pogledu mize s izrezljankami veliki približno 7 slikovnih "
"pik. V tem obsegu je težko videti sliko, barvo, obliko kosa ali celo "
"osvetlitev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&palapeli; has always had a choice of backgrounds and background colors and "
"that helps visibility. Added to these is a more prominent highlighting "
"scheme, which appears if you do not choose shadowing, and a setting to "
"choose the color of the highlight, to contrast with the background and most "
"pieces. Also these settings are now saved and restored with each puzzle. So "
"each puzzle can have the background and highlighting that best suits its "
"overall picture. It is worth experimenting with settings when you create a "
"large puzzle, but you may need to reload or restart the puzzle before all "
"changes can take effect."
msgstr ""
"&palapeli; je vedno imel možnost izbire ozadij in barv ozadja, kar pripomore "
"k vidljivosti. Tem je dodana bolj izrazita shema označevanja, ki se prikaže, "
"če ne izberete senčenja, in nastavitev za izbiro barve označevanja, ki je v "
"kontrastu z ozadjem in večino kosov. Tudi te nastavitve so zdaj shranjene in "
"obnovljene z vsako izrezljamko. Tako ima lahko vsaka izrezljanka ozadje in "
"poudarke, ki najbolj ustrezajo njeni splošni sliki. Vredno je "
"eksperimentirati z nastavitvami, ko ustvarite veliko izrezljanko, vendar "
"boste morda morali znova naložiti ali znova zagnati izrezljanko, preden "
"lahko vse spremembe stopijo v veljavo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using piece-holders"
msgstr "Uporaba držal za kose"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:555
#, no-c-format
msgid "What are piece-holders?"
msgstr "Kaj so držala za kose?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Piece-holders are perhaps the most useful feature of &palapeli; for helping "
"solve large puzzles. They are small, floating windows into which you can "
"sort groups of pieces, such as <quote>edges</quote>, <quote>sky</quote>, "
"<quote>skyline</quote> or <quote>white house on left</quote>. Initially they "
"appear at a minimum size which is just large enough to show four pieces at "
"close-up scale, so they are quite easy to fit in next to the main puzzle "
"table window."
msgstr ""
"Držala za kose so morda najbolj uporabna funkcija &palapeli; za pomoč pri "
"reševanju velikih izrezljank. So majhna, lebdeča okna, v katera lahko "
"razvrstite skupine kosov, kot so <quote>robovi</quote>, <quote>nebo</quote>, "
"<quote>obzorje</quote> ali <quote>bela hiša na levo</quote>. Sprva so "
"prikazani v najmanjši velikosti, ki je ravno dovolj velika, da prikaže štiri "
"dele v merilu od blizu, tako da jih je zelo enostavno namestiti poleg "
"glavnega okna mize izrezljanke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Being windows, holders can be freely moved around the desktop and resized. "
"The <guibutton>Close</guibutton> button will delete the holder, but only if "
"it contains no pieces. The <guibutton>Maximize</guibutton> button will "
"expand or contract the holder rapidly. The holder can contain any number of "
"pieces (maybe hundreds). A maximize action can be useful when reviewing the "
"contents or constructing a sub-assembly inside the holder."
msgstr ""
"Ker so držala okna, jih je mogoče prosto premikati po namizju in jim "
"spreminjati velikost. Gumb <guibutton>Zapri</guibutton> bo izbrisal držalo, "
"vendar le, če ne vsebuje kosov. Gumb <guibutton>Povečaj</guibutton> bo "
"držalo hitro razširil ali skrčil. Držalo lahko vsebuje poljubno število "
"kosov (lahko na stotine). Dejanje povečanja je lahko koristno pri "
"pregledovanju vsebine ali sestavljanju podsklopa znotraj držala."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can have as many holders as you like. There is usually one which is "
"active - outlined in blue. It is the target for actions such as transferring "
"pieces or deleting a holder."
msgstr ""
"Imate lahko poljubno število držal. Običajno je eno aktivno – obrobljeno z "
"modro. Je cilj za dejanja, kot je prenos kosov ali brisanje držala."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:583
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating and deleting holders"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje in brisanje držal"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you start a large puzzle, a holder called <quote>Hand</quote> is "
"created automatically. This may be the only holder you need with puzzles of "
"300 to 750 pieces, but you can have as many holders as you like, even with "
"puzzles of less than 300 pieces."
msgstr ""
"Ko začnete veliko izrezljanko, se samodejno ustvari držalo z imenom "
"<quote>Roka</quote>. To je morda edino držalo, ki ga potrebujete za "
"izrezljanke s 300 do 750 kosi, vendar lahko imate poljubno število držal, "
"tudi za izrezljanke z manj kot 300 kosi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:591
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create or delete a holder, use the <menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>C</"
"keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem> Create Piece Holder…"
"</guimenuitem></menuchoice> or <menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>D</keycap></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Move</guimenu><guimenuitem> Delete Piece Holder</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu items, or simply the <keycap>C</keycap> and "
"<keycap>D</keycap> keys, or the <guibutton>Close</guibutton> button to "
"delete. When you create a holder, you are asked to give it a name, but that "
"is not essential. Usually the holder is at close-up scale and you can easily "
"see what kind of piece is in it."
msgstr ""
"Če želite ustvariti ali izbrisati držalo, uporabite "
"<menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>C</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem> Ustvari držalo kosa...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ali "
"<menuchoice><shortcut><keycap>D</keycap></shortcut> <guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Izbriši držalo kosa</guimenuitem></menuchoice> elemente "
"menija ali preprosto tipki <keycap>C</keycap> in <keycap>D</keycap> ali gumb "
"<guibutton>Zapri</guibutton> za brisanje. Ko ustvarite držalo, ga morate "
"poimenovati, vendar to ni bistveno. Običajno je držalo v merilu od blizu in "
"zlahka vidite, kakšen kos je v njem."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:605
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you delete a holder, it must be active (outlined in blue) and empty of "
"pieces. If the holder to be deleted is not active, click on it. After "
"deletion, there is no active holder, so click on one of those that are left."
msgstr ""
"Ko izbrišete držalo, mora biti aktivno (obrobljeno z modro) in brez kosov. "
"Če držalo, ki ga želite izbrisati, ni aktivno, kliknite nanj. Po izbrisu ni "
"aktivnega držala, zato kliknite na enega od preostalih."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:613
#, no-c-format
msgid "Transferring pieces into and out of holders"
msgstr "Prenašanje kosov v držala in iz njih"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Transferring pieces by dragging and dropping is not possible with holders, "
"nor is it needed. Instead, you can transfer pieces instantly by "
"<quote>teleporting</quote>, as in <quote>Star Trek</quote>. Teleporting "
"works by hold the &Shift; key and click with the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Prenos kosov z vlečenjem in spuščanjem pri držalih ni mogoč, niti ni "
"potreben. Namesto tega lahko dele takoj prenesete s <quote>teleportacijo</"
"quote>, kot v <quote>Zvezdnih stezah</quote>. Teleportacija deluje tako, da "
"držite &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To transfer pieces to a holder, make sure your target holder is active "
"(outlined in blue), then select some pieces on the puzzle table and hold the "
"&Shift; key and click with the &LMB;. Or you can just click on one piece at "
"a time by hold the &Shift; key and click with the &LMB;. The transferred "
"pieces vanish from the puzzle table and reappear, highlighted, in the "
"holder. As they arrive, they are automatically packed into a grid and the "
"last piece transferred is centered in the view."
msgstr ""
"Če želite prenesti dele v držalo, se prepričajte, da je vaše ciljno držalo "
"aktivno (obrobljeno z modro), nato izberite nekaj kosov na mizi izrezljanke "
"in držite &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB;. Lahko pa preprosto kliknete en kos "
"naenkrat tako, da držite &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB;. Preneseni kosi "
"izginejo z mize izrezljanke in se znova prikažejo, označeni, v držalu. Ko "
"prispejo, se samodejno zapakirajo v mrežo in zadnji preneseni kos je na "
"sredini pogleda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To transfer pieces out of a holder, select a piece or pieces inside the "
"holder, then return to the puzzle table and click on an empty spot where you "
"would like the piece(s) to appear, hold the &Shift; key and click with the "
"&LMB;. Avoid clicking on a piece that is already on the puzzle table: it "
"will send the piece to the holder - not what you want. If you accidentally "
"do this with a large joined-up piece (&ie; part of your solution), there is "
"a warning message and an opportunity to cancel."
msgstr ""
"Če želite prenesti dele iz držala, izberite del ali dele znotraj držala, "
"nato se vrnite na mizo izrezljanke in kliknite na prazno mesto, kjer želite, "
"da se pojavijo kos(i), pridržite &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB;. Izogibajte se "
"klikanju na kos, ki je že na mizi izrezljanke: kos bo poslan v držalo - ne "
"tisto, kar želite. Če to pomotoma storite z velikim spojenim kosom (&ie; "
"delom vaše rešitve), se pojavi opozorilno sporočilo in možnost preklica."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:643
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pieces stay highlighted after teleporting. That allows you to reverse the "
"action quickly if you accidentally transfer the wrong pieces or use the "
"wrong holder. Also, on the puzzle table, you can easily adjust the position "
"of a piece or pieces that have just arrived or move a piece into the "
"solution."
msgstr ""
"Kosi po teleportaciji ostanejo označeni. To vam omogoča, da hitro obrnete "
"dejanje, če pomotoma prenesete napačne kose ali uporabite napačno držalo. "
"Prav tako lahko na mizi izrezljanke preprosto prilagodite položaj pravkar "
"prispelega kosa ali kosov ali premaknete delček v rešitev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:651
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Teleporting also works between holders. Start as if you are going to "
"transfer pieces to the puzzle table, but then by hold the &Shift; key and "
"click with the &LMB; in an empty spot in another holder. To reverse the "
"process, go back to the original holder and hold the &Shift; key and click "
"with the &LMB; again."
msgstr ""
"Teleportacija deluje tudi med držali. Začnite, kot da boste prenesli koščke "
"na mizo izrezljanke, nato pa z držanjem &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB; na "
"prazno mesto v drugo držalo. Če želite postopek obrniti, se vrnite na "
"prvotno držalo in držite &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB; ponovno."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:661
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sorting pieces"
msgstr "Razvrščanje kosov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To sort pieces into holders efficiently as you search through a large "
"puzzle, use the technique for stepping through the puzzle a <quote>page</"
"quote> at a time, <link linkend=\"large-puzzle-navigating\"> as described "
"earlier</link>, combined with holders and teleporting to collect pieces as "
"you go. When you have scanned the whole puzzle table, zoom to a close-up of "
"your solution area and place the pieces you have collected. Or you can pre-"
"assemble pieces in holders."
msgstr ""
"Za učinkovito razvrščanje kosov v držala med iskanjem po veliki izrezljanki "
"uporabite tehniko za korakanje po izrezljanki <quote>stran</quote> naenkrat, "
"<link linkend=\"large-puzzle-navigating\">, kot je opisano prej </link>, v "
"kombinaciji z držali in teleportacijo za sprotni zbiranje kosov. Ko "
"pregledate celotno mizo izrezljanke, povečajte območje reševanja od blizu in "
"postavite kose, ki ste jih zbrali. Lahko pa predhodno sestavite kose v "
"držala."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other holder actions"
msgstr "Druga dejanja držala"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Piece-holders support all the functions of the puzzle table (see <link "
"linkend=\"puzzletable-moves\">Basic moves</link>), except that you can only "
"zoom by using the scroll-<mousebutton>wheel</mousebutton> or the &MMB;."
msgstr ""
"Držala za kose podpirajo vse funkcije mize izrezljanke (glejte <link linkend="
"\"puzzletable-moves\">Osnovne poteze</link>), le da lahko povečate le z "
"uporabo <mousebutton>kolesca</mousebutton> ali &MMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:682
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This means that you can use a holder as an extra puzzle table, if you wish. "
"You can drag and drop, join pieces together, move the boundaries of the "
"area, &etc; You can also teleport assembled pieces of any size into or out "
"of a holder, but beware of overlaps or small pieces being hidden."
msgstr ""
"To pomeni, da lahko držalo uporabite kot dodatno izrezljanko, če želite. "
"Lahko povlečete in spustite, združite dele, premikate meje območja itd. Prav "
"tako lahko teleportirate sestavljene kose poljubne velikosti v držalo ali iz "
"njega, vendar pazite na prekrivanja ali skrite majhne koščke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, you can use the <menuchoice><shortcut> <keycap>A</keycap></"
"shortcut><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Select all in holder</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item, followed by <menuchoice><shortcut> "
"<keycap>R</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Rearrange "
"Pieces</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item or hold the &Shift; key and "
"click with the &LMB;, to re-pack all the pieces in the holder or empty all "
"the pieces out onto the puzzle table. Or just use the <keycap>A</keycap> or "
"<keycap>R</keycap> keys on the currently selected holder."
msgstr ""
"Končno lahko uporabite menijski element <menuchoice><shortcut> <keycap>A</"
"keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Premakni</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Izberi vse v "
"držalu</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>, ki mu sledi <menuchoice><shortcut> "
"<keycap>R</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Premakni</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Prerazporedi kose</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> element menija "
"ali držite &Shift; in kliknite z &LMB;, da ponovno zapakirate vse dele v "
"držalo ali izpraznite vse dele na mizo izrezljanke. Ali pa preprosto "
"uporabite tipki <keycap>A</keycap> ali <keycap>R</keycap> na trenutno "
"izbranem držalu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:707
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interface Overview"
msgstr "Pregled vmesnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:708
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following are &palapeli;'s menu items, some of which are also available "
"as action icons in the toolbar and keyboard shortcuts."
msgstr ""
"Sledijo elementi menija &palapeli;, od katerih so nekateri na voljo tudi kot "
"ikone dejanj v orodni vrstici in bližnjice na tipkovnici."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Create New Puzzle…</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Ustvari novo izrezljanko...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Opens a dialog which allows you to create a puzzle from an image on "
"your disk.</action> See <link linkend=\"create-puzzles\">the corresponding "
"section</link> for details and also <link linkend=\"large-puzzle-creation"
"\">special concerns</link>, if you are going to create a puzzle with 300 or "
"more pieces."
msgstr ""
"<action>Odpre pogovorno okno, ki vam omogoča ustvarjanje izrezljanke iz "
"slike na vašem disku.</action> Glejte <link linkend=\"create-puzzles"
"\">ustrezen razdelek</link> za podrobnosti in tudi <link linkend= \"large-"
"puzzle-creation\">posebne skrbi</link>, če boste sestavljali izrezljanko s "
"300 ali več kosi."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import from File…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uvoz iz datoteke...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:719
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export to File…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvozi v datoteko...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:723
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Delete Puzzle</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izbriši izrezljanko</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:727
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Game</guimenu><guimenuitem>Restart Puzzle…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Igra</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovni zagon izrezljanke...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:728
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Re-shuffle all the pieces and discard the saved progress for the current "
"puzzle."
msgstr ""
"Ponovno premešaj vse koščke in zavrzi shranjeni napredek za trenutno "
"izrezljanko."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo> </"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Zapusti</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:732
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Quit</action> the &palapeli;."
msgstr "<action>Zapusti</action> &palapeli;."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:735
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>C</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Create Piece Holder…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>C</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Ustvari držalo za kos...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:736
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a temporary holder for storing or sorting pieces. See <link linkend="
"\"large-puzzle-holders\">Using piece-holders</link> for details of how to "
"use a holder."
msgstr ""
"Ustvarite začasno držalo za shranjevanje ali razvrščanje kosov. Glejte <link "
"linkend=\"large-puzzle-holders\">Uporaba držal za kose</link> za podrobnosti "
"o uporabi držala."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:739
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>D</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Delete Piece Holder</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>D</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Izbriši imetnik kosa</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:740
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete a selected temporary holder when it is empty."
msgstr "Izbriši izbranega začasnega imetnika, ko je prazen."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>A</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Select All in Holder</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>A</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Izberi vse v držalu</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:744
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select all pieces in the currently selected piece-holder (outlined in blue)."
msgstr ""
"Izberite vse kose v trenutno izbranem držalu kosov (obrobljeno z modro)."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:747
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycap>R</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Move</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Rearrange Pieces</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycap>R</keycap></shortcut><guimenu>Premakni</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Prerazporedi kose</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Rearrange selected pieces in any holder or the puzzle table by packing them "
"into a grid."
msgstr ""
"Prerazporedite izbrane kose v poljubnem držalu ali mizi izrezljanke, tako da "
"jih zložite v mrežo."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:751
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Back to Collection</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Nazaj v zbirko</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:756
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preview</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Predogled</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:757
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Toggle the display of the completed puzzle preview image.</action> "
"Hover it with the mouse pointer to zoom in the image."
msgstr ""
"<action>Preklopi prikaz slike za predogled dokončane izrezljanke.</action> "
"Premaknite se z miškinim kazalcem, da povečate sliko."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:760
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>+</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zoom In</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>+</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Povečaj</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:761
#, no-c-format
msgid "Increase the scale."
msgstr "Povečaj lestvico."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:764
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>-</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zoom Out</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>-</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Pomanjšaj</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:765
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrease the scale."
msgstr "Zmanjšajte lestvico."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:768
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Enable All Messages</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Omogoči vsa sporočila</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:769
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allows you to enable all messages disabled by checking the <guilabel>Do not "
"show this message again</guilabel> option in the &palapeli; confirmation "
"dialogs."
msgstr ""
"Omogoča vam, da omogočite vsa sporočila, ki so onemogočena z izbiro možnosti "
"<guilabel>Ne prikaži več tega sporočila</guilabel> v &palapeli; potrditvena "
"pogovorna okna."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Show Statusbar of Puzzle Table</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Prikaži vrstico stanja mize "
"izrezljanke</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:773
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Toggle the display of the progress bar and buttons below the puzzle "
"table.</action> This action will change nothing in the puzzle collection."
msgstr ""
"<action>Preklopi prikaz vrstice napredka in gumbov pod mizo izrezljanke.</"
"action> To dejanje ne bo spremenilo ničesar v zbirki izrezljank."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:776
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &palapeli;…</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj &palapeli;...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:777
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open a game configuration dialog. See <link linkend=\"configuration\">Game "
"Configuration</link> section for more details."
msgstr ""
"Odprite pogovorno okno za konfiguracijo igre. Za več podrobnosti glejte "
"razdelek <link linkend=\"configuration\">Konfiguracija igre</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:781
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally &palapeli; has the common &kde; <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> and "
"<guimenu>Help</guimenu> menu items, for more information read the sections "
"about the <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings"
"\">Settings Menu</ulink> and <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus."
"html#menus-help\">Help Menu</ulink> of the &kde; Fundamentals."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega ima &palapeli; skupno s &kde; Elementi menija "
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> in <guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu>, za več informacij "
"preberite razdelke o <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-"
"settings\">meniju z nastavitvami</ulink> in <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/"
"menus.html#menus-help\">meni Pomoč</ulink> v &kde; Osnove."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:788
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguracija igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:789
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To open the configuration dialog, use the menu item: "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &palapeli;…</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Če želite odpreti konfiguracijsko pogovorno okno, uporabite element menija: "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj "
"&palapeli;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:791
#, no-c-format
msgid "General settings"
msgstr "Splošne nastavitve"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:794
#, no-c-format
msgid "Puzzle table"
msgstr "Miza izrezljanke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:796
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lets you choose some parameters of the puzzle table."
msgstr "Omogoča vam izbiro nekaterih parametrov mize izrezljanke."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:799
#, no-c-format
msgid "Background:"
msgstr "Ozadje:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:800
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Lets you choose another background texture for the puzzle table.</"
"action> If you choose a single color instead of a texture, the button "
"besides the selection box can be used to define the color."
msgstr ""
"<action>Omogoča vam, da izberete drugo teksturo ozadja za mizo izrezljanke.</"
"action> Če izberete eno samo barvo namesto teksture, lahko gumb poleg "
"izbirnega polja uporabite za določitev barve."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:803
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color for highlighting selected pieces:"
msgstr "Barva za poudarjanje izbranih kosov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:804
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Lets you choose the highlighting color of pieces when they are "
"selected.</action> Click on the button to the right of the label to open the "
"<ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/colors.html\">Color Selector</ulink> window."
msgstr ""
"<action>Omogoča vam, da izberete barvo označevanja kosov, ko so izbrani.</"
"action> Kliknite gumb na desni strani oznake, da odprete <ulink url=\"help:/"
"fundamentals/colors.html\">Izbirnik barv </ulink> okno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Space for solution:"
msgstr "Prostor za rešitev:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:808
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Lets you choose where to reserve some space on the puzzle table for "
"building the solution.</action> No space is provided if you select option "
"<guilabel>None</guilabel> or the puzzle has less than 20 pieces. Changes "
"will take effect when a puzzle is created or re-started."
msgstr ""
"<action>Omogoča vam, da izberete, kje želite rezervirati nekaj prostora na "
"mizi izrezljanke za izdelavo rešitve.</action> Prostor ni na voljo, če "
"izberete možnost <guilabel>Brez</guilabel> ali če ima izrezljanka manj kot "
"20 kosov. Spremembe bodo začele veljati, ko je izrezljanka ustvarjena ali "
"znova zagnana."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:811
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spacing of pieces in puzzle grids (1.0-1.5):"
msgstr "Razmik kosov v mrežah izrezljanke (1,0–1,5):"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:812
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Lets you choose the spacing in puzzle grids.</action> Changes in the "
"overall puzzle spacing will take effect only when a puzzle is created or re-"
"started."
msgstr ""
"<action>Omogoča vam, da izberete razmik v mrežah izrezljanke.</action> "
"Spremembe celotnega razmika izrezljanke bodo začele veljati šele, ko je "
"izrezljanka ustvarjena ali znova zagnana."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:818
#, no-c-format
msgid "Piece appearance"
msgstr "Videz kosa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:819
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Controls the appearance of pieces on the puzzle table.</action> If "
"&palapeli; is running slowly or puzzles take a long time to open, you can "
"disable the graphical effects in this category and speed up everything. If "
"you choose shadowing, highlighting is implemented by changing the color of "
"the shadow."
msgstr ""
"<action>Nadzoruje videz kosov na mizi izrezljanke.</action> Če &palapeli; "
"teče počasi ali se izrezljanke dolgo odpirajo, lahko onemogočite grafične "
"učinke v tej kategoriji in pospešite vse. Če izberete senčenje, se "
"poudarjanje izvede s spremembo barve sence."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:822
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapping precision"
msgstr "Natančnost zapenjanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:823
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Lets you choose how closely neighboring pieces must be positioned "
"before they snap together.</action> If you move the slider to the right, "
"pieces will snap together even if they are not so close. This makes the game "
"a bit easier to play."
msgstr ""
"<action>Omogoča vam, da izberete, kako blizu morajo biti sosednji deli "
"nameščeni, preden se spnejo skupaj.</action> Če premaknete drsnik v desno, "
"se bodo deli speli skupaj, tudi če niso tako blizu. To naredi igro nekoliko "
"lažjo za igranje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mouse interaction"
msgstr "Interakcija z miško"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:829
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This page of the configuration dialog allows you to change the assignments "
"of mouse buttons and modifier keys to the actions described in <link linkend="
"\"puzzletable-mouseactions\">Playing on the puzzle table, Mouse "
"interactions</link>. Care should be taken to avoid ambiguous assignments. "
"Three of the default assignments can go to the &LMB; because the pointer is "
"over different areas when you use them, but the other assignments must be "
"distinct."
msgstr ""
"Ta stran konfiguracijskega pogovornega okna vam omogoča, da spremenite "
"dodelitve miškinih gumbov in modifikacijskih tipk za dejanja, opisana v "
"<link linkend=\"puzzletable-mouseactions\">Igranje na mizi izrezljanke, "
"interakcije z miško</link>. Paziti je treba, da se izognete dvoumnim "
"dodelitvam. Tri privzete dodelitve lahko gredo na &LMB; ker je kazalec na "
"različnih področjih, ko jih uporabljate, vendar morajo biti druge dodelitve "
"različne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The interactions are divided into those that can be assigned to mouse "
"buttons (&eg; <action>Move viewport by dragging</action>), and those that "
"can be assigned to the mouse <mousebutton>wheel</mousebutton> (&eg; "
"<action>Scroll viewport horizontally</action>)."
msgstr ""
"Interakcije so razdeljene na tiste, ki jih je mogoče dodeliti miškinim "
"gumbom (&eg; <action>Premakni vidno polje z vlečenjem</action>), in tiste, "
"ki jih je mogoče dodeliti miškinemu <mousebutton>kolescu</mousebutton> (&eg; "
"<action>Pomaknite se po oknu vodoravno</action>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:832
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mouse Buttons tab"
msgstr "Zavihek Gumbi miške"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:833
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To the right of the name of each interaction is a button with a picture of a "
"computer mouse which shows the currently assigned action. You can configure "
"the interaction by clicking on that button with the &LMB; and then with the "
"mouse button which you wish to assign to this interaction. If you hold "
"modifier keys while clicking for the second time, the puzzle table will "
"allow this interaction only while these modifiers are being held."
msgstr ""
"Desno od imena vsake interakcije je gumb s sliko računalniške miške, ki "
"prikazuje trenutno dodeljeno dejanje. Interakcijo lahko konfigurirate s "
"klikom na ta gumb z &LMB; in nato z gumbom miške, ki ga želite dodeliti tej "
"interakciji. Če držite modifikatorske tipke, medtem ko drugič kliknete, bo "
"miza uganke omogočila to interakcijo le, ko so ti modifikatorji pridržani."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:834
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of clicking, you can also press &Space; to assign the special "
"<guilabel>No-Button</guilabel> to this interaction. This is only allowed if "
"modifier keys are being held. The <guilabel>No-Button</guilabel> means that "
"the modifier keys take the role of the mouse button: The interaction starts "
"when the modifier keys are pressed, and stops when one of the modifier keys "
"is released."
msgstr ""
"Namesto klikanja lahko pritisnete &Space; da tej interakciji dodelite "
"poseben <guilabel>Brez gumba</guilabel>. To je dovoljeno samo, če so "
"pridržane modifikacijske tipke. <guilabel>Brez gumba</guilabel> pomeni, da "
"modifikacijske tipke prevzamejo vlogo gumba miške: interakcija se začne, ko "
"pritisnete modifikacijske tipke, in se ustavi, ko eno od modifikacijskih "
"tipk izpustite."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:837
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mouse Wheel tab"
msgstr "Zavihek kolesca miške"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:838
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This tab works similarly to the previous one. When the button on the right "
"asks for input, you have to turn the mouse <mousebutton>wheel</mousebutton> "
"instead of clicking a mouse button. Holding modifier keys is allowed, too, "
"with the same consequences as in the previous case."
msgstr ""
"Ta zavihek deluje podobno kot prejšnji. Ko gumb na desni zahteva vnos, "
"morate obrniti <mousebutton>kolešček</mousebutton> miške, namesto da "
"kliknete gumb miške. Dovoljeno je tudi držanje modifikacijskih tipk z "
"enakimi posledicami kot v prejšnjem primeru."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your mouse has a bidirectional mouse <mousebutton>wheel</mousebutton> (as "
"most commonly found on notebook touchpads), you can take advantage of this: "
"The button will recognize whether you turned the mouse <mousebutton>wheel</"
"mousebutton> horizontally or vertically."
msgstr ""
"Če ima vaša miška dvosmerno <mousebutton>kolešček</mousebutton> (kot ga "
"najpogosteje najdemo na sledilnih ploščicah prenosnih računalnikov), lahko "
"to izkoristite: gumb bo prepoznal, ali ste <mousebutton>kolešček</"
"mousebutton> miške obrnili vodoravno ali navpično."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:845
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credits and License"
msgstr "Zasluge in licenca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:846
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&palapeli; aims to bring the unagitated fun and challenge of jigsaw puzzles "
"to your desktop."
msgstr ""
"&palapeli; želi prenesti nevznemirjeno zabavo in izzive izrezljank na vaše "
"namizje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The idea was first developed by Bernhard Schiffner, together with Stefan "
"Majewsky, who was the leading developer of &palapeli;."
msgstr ""
"Idejo je prvi razvil Bernhard Schiffner skupaj s Stefanom Majewskyjem, ki je "
"bil vodilni razvijalec &palapeli;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:848
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &i18n-psc; was contributed by Johannes L&#xF6;hnert."
msgstr "&i18n-psc; je prispeval Johannes L&#xF6;hnert."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:849
#, no-c-format
msgid "The large-puzzle facilities were contributed by Ian Wadham."
msgstr "Velike izrezljanke je prispeval Ian Wadham."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:850
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Documentation Copyright 2009, 2010 Johannes L&#xF6;hnert, Stefan Majewsky "
"and Copyright 2014 Ian Wadham."
msgstr ""
"Dokumentacija Copyright 2009, 2010 Johannes L&#xF6;hnert, Stefan Majewsky in "
"Copyright 2014 Ian Wadham."

